reviews.comment: Just reiterating that this charger maxes out at 29 kW, not 62.5 kW. Chargepoint is falsely advertising, as usual!
The app authentication process was quick and seamless. The charger is rated at ~62 kwh, but my Ioniq 5 topped out at 56 and has now gone down to 48, even though I'm only at 51% charge.
Only two charges so I had to wait but it is working right now at 27 kilowatts.
Short wait. Chargepoint said 65kw, but was actually 27kw.
Both stations chugging along at 28kW.
Site said 2 of 2 available but both occupied. After short wait, now charging at 27kw.
Both were occupied upon arrival but was able to get in after a short wait.

Consistently ChargePoint falsely advertises this station as 62.5 kW. I figure we should all request refunds of 33% of our charging costs as that is how much more time we will be spending here than they advertise.
Tried charging my Hyundai ionic electric but station said no vehicle detected and then changed to say unable to charge. someone next to me said they tried to charge at station 2 but it was slow.

I'm starting to regret buying an EV. ChargePoint, EV Go and Electrify America are not servicing their infrastructure and it degrades my charging experience very significantly. Why am I stuck at 41 kW? Why is this the only plug in a 20 mile radius at 7 am?

Charger 1 (further away from McDonald's) is running at half speed or slower. It probably needs to have one of its field-replaceable power modules replaced. (It's a quick, 20-minute swap by a field tech, so Mass DOT has no excuse for letting it languish.) Cool that it runs at all when in a failure condition.
Charger 2 (on the right, the closest to McDonald's) is operating well.
Very slow! Only 28kw
Used to hit higher kWh, stuck at 31
Worked well with my credit card. No issues.
These have been reliable lately!
Right charger is working and actually giving nearly 60 kW, what a nice surprise. Chargepoint app thinks the left charger is offline, at a glance it looks like it's operational
Both of the Chargepoint non-Tesla charging stations are working.
No issues.

Great location and reliable. McDs and Gulf Mart. Tesla superchargers right next to the CCS chargers.

To be clear Im referring to the right (if walking out of McD) charger as being reliable sounds like the other one isnt as great.
